npc1: Welcome to what used to be called Sunrise City.
npc1: We don't call it that anymore.
npc1: Three years ago, glowing creatures appeared at night. We called them Bats.
npc1: They didn't attack at first. They just... flashed. Like advertisements. "WIN BIG TONIGHT. FREE CREDITS. GUARANTEED JACKPOT."
npc1: People downloaded the apps they promoted. That's when the Frogs came.
npc1: The Frogs carry slot machine patterns on their skin. One touch and you can't stop fighting them — just like you can't stop spinning.
npc1: When people had nothing left, She arrived. The Witch. Calling herself a lender.
npc1: "I'll help you win it back," she promised. No one ever did.
npc1: Now most of the city belongs to them. The Bats lure, the Frogs hook, the Witch collects.
npc1: But all of them — every single one — they're being controlled by a signal from somewhere deeper.
npc1: From inside the internet itself.
npc1: Someone has to go in and trace it back to the source. Maybe that someone is you.
